            <h3>
             Peter Freund, theoretical physicist and storyteller, 1936-2018
            </h3>
            <p>
             Peter George Oliver Freund—prominent theoretical physicist, fiction writer, lover of the arts, and raconteur—died on March 6, 2018. He was 81. Freund began his career at UChicago as a research associate in 1962 and became a faculty member in 1965. At UChicago, Freund made
             <a href="https://physicstoday.scitation.org/doi/10.1063/PT.3.4171" rel="noreferrer" target="_blank">
              several important contributions
             </a>
             to particle physics and string theory.
